creator: bassam.alshaebani@novartis.com
text:

creator: chip@force-elite.com
bassam.alshaebani@novartis.com
text:
I'm running AIX 5.1 ML06, downloaded apache 2 from www.apache.org. 
I followed the directions in the INSTALL file:
1.  gzip -d httpd-2_0_NN.tar.gz
2.  tar xvf httpd-2_0_NN.tar
3.  gunzip php-NN.tar.gz
4.  tar -xvf php-NN.tar
5.  cd httpd-2_0_NN
6.  ./configure --enable-so
7.  make
8.  make install

The issue was at step 6 (six), once I executed "./configure --enable-so", it 
ran for about 90 minutes, then abended.

creator: chip@force-elite.com
text:
I don't know much about AIX, but can you try:

./configure --enable-so LDFLAGS="-lm"

For your step 6?

creator: trawick@apache.org
text:
look for the section "sqrt unresolved" at 
http://people.apache.org/~trawick/aix_bld_prob.html
